		<title>03Industry</title>
		<content>   John Griffiths of Abercarn purchased
 the mills and lands at Ponthir from   
 Herbert Mackworth for Â£460. The       
 Ponthir tin works were built in 1747, 
 and in that year 'pickling' was       
 introduced. The owner of the tin works
 was John Butler who also owned works  
 at Caerleon and Pontnewydd. In recent 
 years Ponthir tin works were blown up.
 There is little industry here today.  
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
